<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n42002d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n42" href="#n42002d">N42 (VI.B.31)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n42all.htm#n42002d"> 2(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> wafer god</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Chapter 1. The struggle before the Surrender of Womanly Self-respect in the Confessional.]</font> There are two women who ought to be constant objects of the compassion of the disciples of Christ &hellip; &mdash; the Brahmin woman, who, deceived by her priests, burns herself on the corpse of her husband to appease the wrath of her wooden gods; and the Roman Catholic woman, who, not less deceived by her priests, suffers a torture far more cruel and ignominious in the confessional-box, to appease the wrath of her wafer-god. <small> Chiniquy, <a name="CPWC" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CPWC"><cite title="source">The Priest The Woman and The Confessional</cite></a> (n.d.) 1</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c09126e" href="c09all.htm#c09126e">VI.C.09:126(e)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
